The '''African Artists' Foundation''' ('''AAF''') is a [[non-profit organization]], based in [[Lagos, Nigeria]]. It was founded in 2007 by ''Azu Nwagbogu''<ref name="Int">{{cite web|title=The African Artist Foundation promoting Art and Photography|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/07/the-african-artist-foundation-promoting-art-and-photography/|publisher=vanguardngr.com|accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref> to promote [[Nigeria|Nigerian]] and other [[African art]] and artists.<ref>{{cite web|title=NON-FORMAL EDUCATION AFRICAN ARTISTS’ FOUNDATION |url=http://www.contemporaryand.com/blog/institue/african-artists-foundation/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140831221239/http://www.contemporaryand.com/blog/institue/african-artists-foundation/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=31 August 2014 |publisher=contemporaryand.com |accessdate=1 December 2014 }}</ref>
==Projects== AAF started the following projects: * ''[[Lagos Photo]] Festival'' – began in 2010 as the first and only international arts festival of photography in Nigeria.<ref name="Int"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Ghosts, queens and selfies: Fantastical photography from LagosPhoto Festival |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/11/04/world/gallery/lagosphoto-festival-2014/index.html?hpt=hp_c5|publisher=cnn.com|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=LagosPhoto festival 2014 – in pictures|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/gallery/2014/oct/28/lagosphoto-festival-2014-in-pictures|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=LIGHT, CAMERA...PHOTOS! |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/light-camera-photos-/192927/ |publisher=thisdaylive.com |accessdate=24 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224035327/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/light-camera-photos-/192927/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=LagosPhoto Festival|url=http://m.vogue.it/en/people-are-talking-about/vogue-arts/2014/10/lagosphoto|publisher=vogue.it|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> * ''National Art Competition'' – began in 2008, helped artist to expose their work to the target audience.<ref>{{cite web|title=NIGERIAN BREWERIES Plc & AFRICAN ARTISTS’ FOUNDATION (AAF) announce the call for entries for the SIXTH ANNUAL National Art Competition|url=http://www.360nobs.com/2013/05/nigerian-breweries-plc-african-artists-foundation-aaf-announce-the-call-for-entries-for-the-sixth-annual-national-art-competition/|publisher=360nobs.com|accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref> * ''Female Artist's Platform''<ref name="Int"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Female Artists' Platform|url=http://www.africanartists.org/programme/female-artists-platform|publisher=africanartists.org|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> * ''CDI – Capacity Development Integration''<ref>{{cite web|title=CDI (Capacity Development Integration)|url=http://www.africanartists.org/programme/cdi-capacity-development-integration|publisher=africanartists.org|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> * ''YECA – Youth Empowerment through Contemporary Art''<ref>{{cite web|title=YECA (Youth Empowerment through Contemporary Art)|url=http://www.africanartists.org/programme/yeca-youth-empowerment-through-contemporary-art|publisher=africanartists.org|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> * ''ABA – Art Base Africa'', it is an online platform for debating about African contemporary art''<ref>{{cite web|title=Art Base Africa|url=http://www.africanartists.org/programme/art-base-africa|publisher=africanartists.org|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> * ''NAC – National Art Competition'', an annual arts competition organized by AAF''<ref>{{cite web|title=National Art Competition (NAC)|url=http://www.africanartists.org/programme/national-art-competition-nac|publisher=africanartists.org|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>
