{{Nauru-stub}}

The '''Gilbertese dancing''', which is accompanied by singing, is a characteristic dance style of the [[Melanesia]]ns and the [[Polynesia]]ns. It is a fusion of folk and [[ballad]] dance forms. Rhythm in the music is accentuated by beating with hand the upturned wooden boxes.<ref name="Grantham2011">{{cite book|author=Alexander Grantham|title=Via Ports: From Hong Kong to Hong Kong|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LNNhhpkKJ10C&pg=PA85|accessdate=8 August 2013|date=1 December 2011|publisher=Hong Kong University Press|isbn=978-988-8083-85-5|pages=85–}}</ref>
