| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|Vassilis|Paleokostas}}
|On June 6, 2006, Nikos Paleokostas and another man hijacked a helicopter, forcing it to land on the roof of the [[Korydallos Prison]]. Two convicts scrambled on, Nikos’s brother, [[Vassilis Paleokostas]] who was sentenced to a 25-year sentence for kidnapping and bank robbery and Alket Rizai, who was serving a life sentence for manslaughter. The helicopter flew to a nearby graveyard from where they fled on motorcycles.<ref name="korydallos">{{cite news | date = June 4, 2006| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/pr/fr/-/1/hi/world/europe/5046986.stm | title = Two flee Greek jail in helicopter | publisher = BBC News| accessdate = 4 June 2006}}</ref>
