|{{sort|2007-07-15|July 15, 2007}}
|Grasse prison
|{{flag|France}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|Pascal|Payet}}
|[[Pascal Payet]], 43, escaped for the third time from Grasse prison using a helicopter that was hijacked by four masked men from [[Cannes - Mandelieu Airport|Cannes-Mandelieu airport (CEQ)]].<ref name="Grasse"/>  The helicopter landed some time later at [[Brignoles]], {{convert|38|km|mi}} north-east of [[Toulon]], [[France]] on the [[Mediterranean]] coast.

Payet and his accomplices then fled the scene and the pilot was released unharmed. Payet gained notoriety for using a helicopter in 2001 to escape from [[Luynes, Bouches-du-Rhône|Luynes]] prison in southern France and then while still on the run in 2003 organized another escape for fellow inmates from the same Luynes prison. Payet had been serving a 30-year sentence for a murder committed during a robbery on a security van.<ref name="SMHau">{{cite news|date=July 15, 2007 |url=http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,22077296-5006003,00.html |title=Killer stages second helicopter prison break |publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)]] |accessdate=July 15, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070717224114/http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0%2C22049%2C22077296-5006003%2C00.html |archivedate=July 17, 2007 |df= }}</ref>
