|{{sort|2009-02-22|February 22, 2009}}
|Korydallos Prison
|{{flag|Greece}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|Vasilis|Paleokostas}}<br />Alket Rizai
|On February 22, 2009 [[Vasilis Paleokostas]] and another man (Alket Rizai) escaped from [[Korydallos Prison]] by helicopter. They had escaped in a similar manner during 2006 but they were eventually arrested. Their new prison break took place while their trial for the 2006 helicopter-assisted escape was ongoing. They were transferred to [[Korydallos Prison]] just one day before their new escape, in order to attend their trial.<ref name="BBC">{{cite news |date=February 22, 2009|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/5046986.stm|title = Prison break repeat shocks Greece |publisher = BBC news| accessdate = May 28, 2009|quote=}}</ref> Alket Rizai was recaptured in November 2009. Vasilis Paleokostas remains a fugitive.
