|{{sort|2009-04-27|April 27, 2009}}
|Domenjod Prison, Réunion
|{{flag|France}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|<br />Alexin Jismy<br />Fabrice Michel
|Juliano Verbard was a guru of the ''Sorrowful and Immaculate Heart of Mary'' launched in 2002 on the island of [[Réunion]], a French territory in the [[Indian Ocean]]. He was arrested and jailed 15&nbsp;years<ref name="BBC_8021789">{{cite news |date=April 27, 2009|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/8021789.stm|title = Cult leader escapes jail in helicopter|publisher = BBC News| accessdate =  May 23, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref> in February 2008 for attacks on children aged nine and 13.<ref name="News.com.au_25394441">{{cite news |date=April 27, 2009|url = http://www.news.com.au/perthnow/story/0,21598,25394441-950,00.html|title = Pedophile cult leader Juliano Verbard escapes from Reunion prison|publisher = [[The Sunday Times (Western Australia)|The Sunday Times]]| accessdate = May 23, 2009 | last=correspondents in Saint Denis |quote=}}</ref>

On April 27, 2009, Juliano Verbard escaped from the Domenjod Prison near [[Saint-Denis, Réunion|Saint-Denis]] on the island of Réunion. Three armed accomplices, posing as tourists, hijacked a helicopter and landed in the exercise yard of the prison.<ref name="france24_04-2009">{{cite web|date=April 27, 2009 |url=http://www.france24.com/en/20090427-cult-leader-escapes-french-jail-helicopter |title=Cult leader escapes from French jail in helicopter |publisher=[[FRANCE 24]] |accessdate=May 28, 2009 |last=Idris Issa |quote= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430113008/http://www.france24.com/en/20090427-cult-leader-escapes-french-jail-helicopter |archivedate=April 30, 2009 }}</ref> He escaped with two followers, father and son duo, Alexin Jismy and Fabrice Michel. Once the three were aboard they took off and landed in a nearby clearing where a van was waiting.<ref name="france24_04-2009"/> He was recaptured on May 6, 2009.<ref name="BBC_8037082">{{cite news |date= 6 May 2009|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/8037082.stm|title = Escaped cult leader re-captured|publisher = BBC News| accessdate = 23 May 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref>
